summary.incident:
Goal! Desire Doue displays great vision
and sends a pass to Achraf Hakimi (PSG),
who shows brilliant composure inside the
box to bury the ball from close range in
the back of the net. The score is 1:0.

Goal! Ousmane Dembele plays it to Desire
Doue (PSG), whose deflected shot from inside
the box goes past the helpless Yann Sommer.
2:0.

Substitution. Yann Bisseck (Inter) in, Benjamin
Pavard out.

Simone Inzaghi has decided to make a change.
Nicola Zalewski (Inter) replaces Federico
Dimarco.

Nicola Zalewski (Inter) can't expect anything
else than a yellow card for his hard tackle.
And a yellow it is. Istvan Kovacs didn't
think twice about pulling it out of his
pocket.

Referee Istvan Kovacs has finally had enough
of Simone Inzaghi and brandishes a yellow
card at him!

Substitution. Henrikh Mkhitaryan makes his
way off the pitch and Carlos Augusto (Inter)
comes on as his replacement.

Yann Bisseck (Inter) is being substituted
because of an injury. Simone Inzaghi sends
Matteo Darmian on the pitch.

What a goal! Vitinha plays it to Desire
Doue (PSG), who finds himself unmarked inside
the box and slots a first-time shot past
Yann Sommer into the bottom right corner.
3:0.

Desire Doue (PSG) behaves unsportingly.
Desire Doue (PSG) is literally asking for
a yellow card with his behaviour. The referee
agrees and books him.

The referee stops play so that a substitution
can be made and Desire Doue trots off the
pitch and is replaced by Bradley Barcola
(PSG).

Istvan Kovacs shows a yellow card to Marcus
Thuram (Inter), who isn't surprised as the
tackle was really hard and late.

Substitution. Hakan Calhanoglu will be replaced
by Kristjan Asllani (Inter).

Istvan Kovacs shows the yellow card to Francesco
Acerbi (Inter) for a heavy challenge.

Goal - 4:0! Ousmane Dembele tees up Khvicha
Kvaratskhelia (PSG) inside the box and he
curls the ball into the left side of the
net and past Yann Sommer.

The referee stops play so that a substitution
can be made and Lucas Hernandez (PSG) comes
onto the pitch for Nuno Mendes.

The referee signals that it is time for
a substitution and Goncalo Ramos (PSG) will
replace Khvicha Kvaratskhelia.

Luis Enrique has decided to substitute Fabian
Ruiz and he is replaced by Senny Mayulu
(PSG).

The referee signals that it is time for
a substitution and Warren Zaire-Emery (PSG)
comes onto the pitch so that Joao Neves
can be given a rest.

Sensational! Senny Mayulu (PSG) shows off
his superb ability as he volleys the ball
from inside the box onto the left post and
in the net. The assist goes to Bradley Barcola
and the score changes to 5:0.

Achraf Hakimi (PSG) commits a foul and is
shown a yellow card without any hesitation
from the referee.

Nuno Mendes (PSG) has tested the patience
of referee Felix Zwayer and goes into the
book for a previous late challenge.

Declan Rice (Arsenal) has to be very careful
for the rest of the match after receiving
a yellow card from the referee for a bad
tackle on an opponent.

Goal! Fabian Ruiz (PSG) picks up the ball
from a rebound and from the edge of the
box he unleashes a shot inside the right
post. It's 1:0.

Myles Lewis-Skelly (Arsenal) shouldn't be
surprised it's a yellow from the ref, who
cooled the situation down well.

A substitution has been made. Myles Lewis-Skelly
goes off and Riccardo Calafiori (Arsenal)
comes on.

Mikel Arteta has decided to introduce fresh
legs, with Leandro Trossard (Arsenal) replacing
Gabriel Martinelli.

Vitinha (PSG) wastes a huge opportunity
to score from the penalty spot. He attempts
to slot into the bottom right corner, but
David Raya pulls off a superb save.

Today's match ends for Bradley Barcola who
will be replaced by Ousmane Dembele (PSG).

Fantastic team goal! Achraf Hakimi (PSG)
was set free in the area by Ousmane Dembele
and made no mistake with a lovely finish
into the right side of the net. 2:0.

Luis Enrique decides to make a substitution.
Desire Doue will be replaced by Lucas Hernandez
(PSG).

Goal! 2:1. The ball rebounds to Bukayo Saka
(Arsenal) after a melee in the box, and
he easily beats the keeper from close range.

Here comes a substitution. Jurrien Timber
is given a rest as he is replaced by Ben
White (Arsenal).

Riccardo Calafiori (Arsenal) is cautioned
and receives a yellow card.

Khvicha Kvaratskhelia (PSG) receives a yellow
card.

Bukayo Saka (Arsenal) criticises the decision
of the referee and immediately receives
a yellow card.

Nuno Mendes goes off the pitch and Goncalo
Ramos (PSG) comes on.

Goal! Denzel Dumfries produces a great pass
that finds Lautaro Martinez (Inter) inside

It must be a yellow card. It is. Hakan Calhanoglu

Inigo Martinez (Barcelona) is shown a yellow

It's a goal! Eric Garcia (Barcelona) scores

Substitution. Federico Dimarco makes way

Goal! Gerard Martin picks out Dani Olmo

The referee signals that it is time for
a substitution and Matteo Darmian (Inter)

Simone Inzaghi has decided to substitute

The referee stops play so that a substitution

Here's the change. Henrikh Mkhitaryan leaves

We are about to witness a substitution.

Goal! Raphinha (Barcelona) was in the right

(Barcelona) is brought on as a substitute

It's 3:3! Denzel Dumfries feeds Francesco

Hansi Flick isn't happy on the touchline

Carlos Augusto (Inter) commits a foul and

The referee stops play so that a substitution

Goal Davide Frattesi (Inter)! Davide Frattesi

Goal! Raphinha gets to the ball and heads

Francois Letexier shows a yellow card to

Bukayo Saka (Arsenal) places the ball on

Goal! It's a catastrophic error from the

Marcus Rashford is in a good shooting position,

a deserved yellow card for his ugly tackle.

Goal! Jurrien Timber (Arsenal) ran onto
a clever lofted pass from Declan Rice and
easily beat the keeper with a header into
the top right corner from close range. 0:1.

who plays a vital role in the build-up.
He squares it to Ethan Nwaneri (Arsenal),
who beats Walter Benitez with a brilliant

Jesus Manzano has issued a yellow card to

Substitution. Luuk de Jong makes his way

summary.incident:

What a goal! Lois Openda plays it to Christoph

Adi Hutter prepares a substitution. Eliesse
Ben Seghir is replaced by Mohammed Salisu
(Monaco).

That's the end of the game for Florentino,
who is replaced by Zeki Amdouni (Benfica).

It will be a substitution. Arthur Cabral
(Benfica) is ready to enter the pitch as
Vangelis Pavlidis walks off.

Goal! A precise cut back on the goal line
from Christian Mawissa Elebi finds Soungoutou
Magassa (Monaco) right in front of goal,
and he easily buries the ball into the bottom
left corner. 2:1.

Yellow card! It's like Christian Mawissa
Elebi (Monaco) was asking for a caution
with his behaviour. Rade Obrenovic agrees
and books him.

Goal! Arthur Cabral (Benfica) makes the
score 2:2 after burying a close-range header
into the roof of the net after a good run
and cross by Angel Di Maria.

Bruno Lage has decided to make a change.
Leandro Barreiro (Benfica) replaces Fredrik
Aursnes.

Goal! Angel Di Maria swings the ball deep
into the box and finds Zeki Amdouni (Benfica)
unmarked, and his close-range header flies
past the keeper into the roof of the net.
2:3.

Substitution. George Ilenikhena (Monaco)
in, Denis Zakaria out.

Here is a change. Angel Di Maria is going
off and Bruno Lage gives the last tactical
orders to Benjamin Rollheiser (Benfica).

Goal! Danylo Sikan (Shakhtar) beautifully
controls a strongly hit pass from Yukhym
Konoplya inside the box. He cuts inside
his marker and rifles the ball into the
bottom left corner. 0:1.

Goal! Yukhym Konoplya displays great vision
and sends a pass to Oleksandr Zubkov (Shakhtar),
who shows brilliant composure inside the
box to bury the ball into the bottom left
corner. The score is 0:2.

The teams are back out for the second half
and here is a change on the pitch. Peter
Bosz gives a chance to Ricardo Pepi (PSV)
and Matteo Dams is off.

The referee stops play so that a substitution
can be made and Danylo Sikan trots off the
pitch and is replaced by Eguinaldo (Shakhtar).

Olivier Boscagli (PSV) attempts to discuss
the decision with Urs Schnyder, but he soon
realises that it's not the right thing to
do as he sees the yellow.

The referee allows time for a substitution.
Noa Lang will be replaced by Guus Til (PSV).

Marino Pusic prepares a substitution. Oleksandr
Zubkov is replaced by Taras Stepanenko (Shakhtar).

Pedrinho (Shakhtar) is shown a red card
by the referee for chasing his opponent
and bringing him down with a very nasty
tackle!

The manager makes a subsitution with Bartol
Franjic (Shakhtar) coming on for Kevin.

Here is a change. Olivier Boscagli is going
off and Peter Bosz gives the last tactical
orders to Hirving Lozano (PSV).

This yellow card was deserved. The tackle
by Ismael Saibari (PSV) was quite harsh
and Urs Schnyder didn't hesitate to show
him a yellow card.

Dmytro Kryskiv (Shakhtar) is punished with
the yellow card.

Malik Tillman (PSV) takes the free kick
with a powerful low drive that goes inside
the right-hand post and ends up behind the
goalkeeper. A real jaw dropper!

Substitution. Richard Ledezma (PSV) in,
Rick Karsdorp out.

What a beautiful moment! Malik Tillman (PSV)
got to the ball and unleashed a strong shot
from distance. It turned out to be a good
decision as his effort found its way into
the top left corner. Dmytro Riznyk just
shakes his head in disbelief. The score
changes to 2:2.

Urs Schnyder has issued a yellow card to
Malik Tillman (PSV).

Ricardo Pepi (PSV) has a golden opportunity
after receiving a beautiful pass. He keeps
his cool and takes a low shot which ricochets
in off the left post.

Marino Pusic (Shakhtar) picks up a yellow
card for unsporting behaviour after the
half-time whistle. He should have gone straight
into the dressing room instead.

Goal! Enzo Millot gets to the ball and heads
it over the defence to Ermedin Demirovic
(VfB Stuttgart), who meets it nicely and
fires in into the back of the net. 0:1.

Goal! Silas (Crvena zvezda) weaves his way
past opponents, and he unleashes a magnificent
effort from the edge of the box into the
bottom right corner. Alexander Nubel had
no chance of reaching it. The score is 1:1.

The Stuttgart players can't believe it after
the referee disallows the goal after the
intervention of the VAR!

Rade Krunic (Crvena zvezda) meets a perfect
cross from Young-Woo Seol deep inside the
box and controls it with a nice first touch.
He produces an accurate strike into the
top left corner. It's 2:1.

Andrija Maksimovic (Crvena zvezda) will
have to be careful for the rest of the match
as he is shown a yellow card.

Anthony Rouault (VfB Stuttgart) receives
a yellow card from the referee for dissent.

Cherif Ndiaye (Crvena zvezda) is booked
after bringing down an opponent. Erik Lambrechts
had an easy-decision to make.

Here comes a substitution. Pascal Stenzel
is given a rest as he is replaced by Fabian
Rieder (VfB Stuttgart).

Erik Lambrechts shows a yellow card to Rade
Krunic (Crvena zvezda) for his blatant foul.

It is time for a substitution. Mirko Ivanic
(Crvena zvezda) is on for Andrija Maksimovic.

Mirko Ivanic (Crvena zvezda) jumped highest
to meet a perfectly executed corner kick
by Timi Elsnik. His header was precise and
ended up in the back of the net, leaving
the goalkeeper flapping in the wind. The
score is 3:1.

The referee stops play so that a substitution
can be made and Milson leaves the pitch
and Nemanja Radonjic (Crvena zvezda) comes
on.

Vladan Milojevic has decided to make a change.
Bruno Duarte (Crvena zvezda) replaces Cherif
Ndiaye.

GOAL! A great pass finds Nemanja Radonjic
(Crvena zvezda) in acres of space after
a fine counter attack. He brings the ball
under control before firing it past the
helpless keeper from close range. Its now
4:1.

It will be a substitution. Jarzinho Malanga
(VfB Stuttgart) is ready to enter the pitch
as Enzo Millot walks off.

Sebastian Hoeness has decided to introduce
fresh legs, with Leonidas Stergiou (VfB
Stuttgart) replacing Josha Vagnoman.

Guelor Kanga (Crvena zvezda) joins the action
as a substitute, replacing Silas.

The manager makes a subsitution with Dalcio
(Crvena zvezda) coming on for Silas.

Substitution. Angelo Stiller is replaced
by Yannik Keitel (VfB Stuttgart).

Sebastian Hoeness prepares a substitution.
Chris Fuhrich is replaced by Benjamin Boakye
(VfB Stuttgart).

Goal - 5:1! Timi Elsnik tees up Nemanja
Radonjic (Crvena zvezda) inside the box
and he rolls the ball into the bottom left
corner and past Alexander Nubel.

The referee shows a yellow card to Jusuf
Gazibegovic (Sturm Graz). No wonder. A clear
yellow for bad language.

It's time for a substitution. Yaser Asprilla
(Girona) comes on in place of Ivan Martin.

Goal! Mika Biereth (Sturm Graz) fires the
rebound into the bottom right corner after
the ball breaks to him in the box. The score
is 1:0.

Bryan Gil (Girona) shouldn't be surprised
it's a yellow from the ref, who cooled the
situation down well.

Here's the change. Malick Yalcouye leaves
the pitch and Tomi Horvat (Sturm Graz) comes
on as a substitute.

Jurgen Saumel has decided to make a change.
Erencan Yardimci (Sturm Graz) replaces Seedy
Jatta.

We are about to witness a subsitution. Cristhian
Stuani (Girona) for Bojan Miovski.

Substitution. Daley Blind is replaced by
Arnaut Danjuma (Girona).

The substitution is prepared. Jhon Elmer
Solis Romero (Girona) joins the action as
a substitute, replacing Alejandro Frances.

Michel has decided to introduce fresh legs,
with Abel Ruiz (Girona) replacing Viktor
Tsygankov.

Substitution. Jon Gorenc Stankovic (Sturm
Graz) replaces Mika Biereth.

Jurgen Saumel has decided to substitute
William Boving and he is replaced by Stefan
Hierlander (Sturm Graz).

summary.incident:
GOAL! Thats a great strike from the spot
by Robert Lewandowski (Barcelona) low into
the right of the net, giving goalkeeper
Marco Bizot no chance!

Kenny Lala (Brest) was probably a bit loose
with his words to Irfan Peljto, who decides
to show him a yellow.

Substitution. Abdallah Sima makes his way
off the pitch and Mama Balde (Brest) comes
on as his replacement.

Mahdi Camara (Brest) commits a foul and
is shown a yellow card without any hesitation
from the referee.

Dani Olmo (Barcelona) latches on to a precise
pass deep inside the box from Gerard Martin,
and he beats the goalkeeper with a low shot
into the middle of the goal. He makes it
2:0.

Hansi Flick has decided to substitute Dani
Olmo and he is replaced by Gavi (Barcelona).

The referee stops play so that a substitution
can be made and Romain Faivre (Brest) comes
onto the pitch for Mahdi Camara.

Kamory Doumbia will be replaced by Mathias
Pereira Lage (Brest).

Ludovic Ajorque (Brest) is booked after
bringing down an opponent. Irfan Peljto
had an easy-decision to make.

The referee signals that it is time for
a substitution and Jonas Martin (Brest)
is coming onto the pitch as Edimilson Fernandes
cannot continue after picking up an injury.

Eric Roy has decided to introduce fresh
legs, with Romain Del Castillo (Brest) replacing
Ludovic Ajorque.

The referee stops play so that a substitution
can be made and Gerard Martin leaves the
pitch and Alejandro Balde (Barcelona) comes
on.

Hansi Flick has decided to make a change.
Pablo Torre (Barcelona) replaces Fermin
Lopez.

Irfan Peljto shows a yellow card to Julien
Le Cardinal (Brest) for his blatant foul.

Here comes a substitution. Frenkie de Jong
(Barcelona) is brought on as a substitute
for Pedri.

Goal! Great link up play between Robert
Lewandowski (Barcelona) and Alejandro Balde
gives the former a clear sight of goal on
the edge of the box. He doesn't disappoint
and beats the keeper in the bottom right
corner. 3:0.

GOAL! Thats a perfect strike from the spot
by Florian Wirtz (Bayer Leverkusen) into
the top right hand corner, giving goalkeeper
Alexander Schlager no chance!

Alejandro Grimaldo (Bayer Leverkusen) scores
a great goal from the resulting free kick
from mid-range. He sends the ball directly
inside the left post.

Problems for Pepijn Lijnders as Karim Konate
is not able to play anymore. His injury

replaces him.

An amazing individual effort from Florian
Wirtz (Bayer Leverkusen) ends with a strike
from inside the penalty area. He sends the
ball precisely into the bottom right corner
and makes it 3:0. Alexander Schlager was
helpless.

Pepijn Lijnders makes a switch. Daouda Guindo
is coming on in place of Aleksa Terzic (Salzburg)
at the start of the second period.

The game is over for Lucas Gourna-Douath
(Salzburg). Stefan Bajcetic comes on for
the second half.

Pepijn Lijnders has decided to make a substitution
during the half-time break. Mads Bidstrup
comes on the pitch for Bobby Clark (Salzburg).

A yellow card for a tackle by Moussa Kounfolo
Yeo (Salzburg). Mikola Balakin doesn't hesitate
at all to make this decision.

Goal! Patrik Schick (Bayer Leverkusen) finds
some space inside the box to meet a beautiful
cross and fires the ball inside the back
of the net.

Robert Andrich (Bayer Leverkusen) is awarded
a yellow card. The referee showed him no
mercy.

The referee stops play so that a substitution
can be made and Exequiel Palacios departs
the field of play to be replaced by Aleix
Garcia (Bayer Leverkusen).

Xabi Alonso has decided to make a change.
Arthur (Bayer Leverkusen) replaces Piero
Hincapie.

The referee stops play so that a substitution
can be made and Nathan Tella (Bayer Leverkusen)
comes onto the pitch for Jeremie Frimpong.

Goal! Great link up play between Aleix Garcia
(Bayer Leverkusen) and Florian Wirtz gives
the former a clear sight of goal on the
edge of the box. He doesn't disappoint and
beats the keeper in the right side of the
goal. 5:0.

Xabi Alonso has decided to introduce fresh
legs, with Artem Stepanov (Bayer Leverkusen)
replacing Patrik Schick.

It will be a substitution. Nicolas Capaldo
(Salzburg) is ready to enter the pitch as

Here comes a substitution. Florian Wirtz

The main referee, Istvan Kovacs, is apparently

Min-Jae Kim (Bayern Munich) gets to the

Ousmane Dembele (PSG) must have known he

Achraf Hakimi (PSG) argues with the referee

The manager has decided to make a substitution

Kingsley Coman (Bayern Munich) is awarded

A substitution has been made. Leroy Sane

Vincent Kompany has decided to introduce

The referee signals a substitution. Goncalo

The foul by Michael Olise (Bayern Munich)

Luis Enrique has decided to substitute Fabian

Istvan Kovacs shows a yellow card to Serge

Fabian Ruiz (PSG) gets a yellow card after

Benjamin Pavard (Inter) is awarded a yellow

OWN GOAL! The free kick is whipped in and

Joao Pinheiro shows the yellow card to Alessandro

Christoph Baumgartner (RB Leipzig) has tested
the patience of referee Joao Pinheiro and

Simone Inzaghi is forced to make a change.
Benjamin Pavard (Inter) is not able to carry

Substitution. Assan Ouedraogo (RB Leipzig)

Substitution. Amadou Haidara makes his way

Simone Inzaghi has decided to make a change.
Carlos Augusto (Inter) replaces Alessandro

Simone Inzaghi has decided to introduce

Substitution. Marko Arnautovic (Inter) has

A yellow card for a tackle by Castello Lukeba

The referee signals a substitution. Viggo

GOAL! Thats a great strike from the spot

It's in the back of the net! Ilkay Gundogan

Fantastic team goal! Erling Haaland (Manchester

Julian Carranza (Feyenoord) is booked after

Pep Guardiola has decided to make a change.

Substitution. Phil Foden walks off the pitch

Brian Priske has decided to substitute Bart

Goal! A mistake from the defence gifted

The ball finds its way to Santiago Tomas
Gimenez (Feyenoord) after a confusing situation
inside the goalmouth. He finds some space

James McAtee (Manchester City) receives

Goal! Igor Paixao hands David Hancko (Feyenoord)

Gabriel (Arsenal) meets the corner and displays

Goncalo Inacio (Sporting Lisbon) gets on

David Raya (Arsenal) gets booked for the

Today's match ends for Marcus Edwards who

Tiago Teixeira decides to make a substitution.

Filip Ugrinic takes over corner duties and

Goal - 1:2! Charles De Ketelaere (Atalanta)

It's a goal! Mateo Retegui (Atalanta) scores

Ebrima Colley (Young Boys) can't expect

Marco Brescianini (Atalanta) is literally

Here is a change after the half-time break.
Ebrima Colley is replaced by Alan Virginius

GOAL 1:5! Charles De Ketelaere (Atalanta)

Substitution. Silvere Ganvoula makes way

Gian Piero Gasperini prepares a substitution.

The referee stops play so that a substitution

Here is a change. Joel Monteiro is going
off and Joel Magnin gives the last tactical
orders to Meschack Elia (Young Boys).

A yellow card for a tackle by Meschack Elia
(Young Boys). Manfredas Lukjancukas doesn't
hesitate at all to make this decision.

Charles De Ketelaere goes off the pitch
and Marco Palestra (Atalanta) comes on.

Gian Piero Gasperini has decided to introduce
fresh legs, with Rafael Toloi (Atalanta)
replacing Sead Kolasinac.

The referee signals that it is time for
a substitution and Zachary Athekame (Young
Boys) is coming onto the pitch as Jaouen
Hadjam cannot continue after picking up
an injury.

The referee signals a substitution. Ben
Godfrey (Atalanta) is brought on as a substitute

Lazar Samardzic (Atalanta) makes a great

Goal! Tammy Abraham displays great vision

What a goal that is! Tigran Barseghyan (Slovan

Paulo Fonseca has decided to make a substitution

Jose Sanchez shows a yellow card to Samuel

Jose Sanchez shows the yellow card to Davide

Idjessi Metsoko is replaced by Danylo Ignatenko

Rafael Leao (AC Milan) receives the ball
inside the box, reacts quickly and without

Goal! It's a catastrophic error from the
opponent which has gifted a chance to Tammy
Abraham (AC Milan), who rolls the ball into
the back of the net from close range. 1:3.

Substitution. Emerson Royal (AC Milan) replaces
Davide Calabria.

Paulo Fonseca has decided to substitute
Christian Pulisic and he is replaced by
Ruben Loftus-Cheek (AC Milan).

Here comes a substitution. Yunus Musah (AC
Milan) is brought on as a substitute for
Youssouf Fofana.

Substitution. Siemen Voet walks off the
pitch and Nino Marcelli (Slovan Bratislava)

Juraj Kucka will be replaced by Marko Tolic
(Slovan Bratislava).

The foul by Fikayo Tomori (AC Milan) is
worthy of a card and a yellow is duly shown
by Jose Sanchez.

Substitution. Tammy Abraham will be replaced
by Francesco Camarda (AC Milan).

Goal! Great play by Tigran Barseghyan releases
Nino Marcelli (Slovan Bratislava) in space

Here is a change. Kyriakos Savvidis is going
off and Vladimir Weiss gives the last tactical
orders to Robert Mak (Slovan Bratislava).

Marko Tolic (Slovan Bratislava) sees a yellow!
His tackle wasn't that harsh, but he probably
talked himself into Jose Sanchez's book.

Yet another yellow card and Marko Tolic
(Slovan Bratislava) is sent off for talking

It's a goal! Julian Alvarez (Atl. Madrid)

GOAL! Marcos Llorente (Atl. Madrid) sends

the field of play to be replaced by Jarell

Vinicius Junior (Real Madrid) converts the

Substitution. Luka Modric did his best and

Vinicius Junior (Real Madrid) is shown a

Rafael Leao feeds the ball through to Tijjani

The referee looks satisfied after his VAR
review and duly disallows the goal for offside.
The Real Madrid players look gutted.

This yellow card was deserved. The tackle
by Youssouf Fofana (AC Milan) was quite
harsh and Slavko Vincic didn't hesitate
to show him a yellow card.

Paulo Fonseca prepares a substitution. Emerson

GOAL! A terrible mistake leads to a goal.

Superb finishing from Maximiliano Araujo

A yellow card for a tackle by Pedro Goncalves

Erling Haaland (Manchester City) fails to

Arnau Martinez (Girona) should have been
more careful. He commits a bad foul, receives

easy-decision to make.

Malik Tillman passes to Johan Bakayoko (PSV),

The referee demonstrates he won't tolerate

summary.incident:
